Qualifications:
1. Responsible for the overall day-to-day operations of a specific property, including supervision of all office and maintenance personnel.
2. Initiate and implement policies, procedures, forms, schedules, and/or controls as necessary to properly manage the property and on-site staff under the direction and approval of the Asset Manager.
3. Supervise the performance of all property staff including the preparation of annual performance reviews;
4. Participate in selection of site employees with Asset Manager and assume primary responsibility for employee advertising and preliminary interviewing;
5. Train Assistant Community Manager, Leasing Consultant and maintenance personnel;
...

1. Bachelor's degree in Business, Public Administration, Finance, Accounting, or a related field;
2. At least one year of experience in financial analysis, budget development/oversight or similar;
3. Any combination of education, professional, volunteer and lived experience that provides the necessary knowledge, skills, and abilities to perform the classification duties and responsibilities.
